    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-03-30T13:38:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-03-30T13:38:00-05:00" n="211"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">315/3–3053: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-03-30T13:38:00-05:00"
                            >March 30, 1953—1:38 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 508. Eyes only for the Secretary. Re
                        <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SyG</gloss>. <persName corresp="#p_ZORINVA1"
                        >Zorin</persName> announced at Big Five meeting that his government would be
                    ready to support <persName corresp="#p_HAMMARSKJOLDD1">Hammarskjold</persName>
                    for <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss>. I stated I had heard nothing against
                        <persName corresp="#p_HAMMARSKJOLDD1">Hammarskjold</persName>, that I would
                    not veto him and that I would seek instructions. On basis of my sketchy
                    information about Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HAMMARSKJOLDD1"
                        >Hammarskjold</persName>, I am inclined to think that he would be
                    satisfactory and that he may be as good as we can get. <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZORINVA1">Zorin</persName> appears to be in a big hurry.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_HOPPENOTH1">Hoppenot</persName> announced intention to
                    vote for <persName corresp="#p_HAMMARSKJOLDD1">Hammarskjold</persName>.
                        <persName corresp="#p_JEBBSHMG1">Jebb</persName> is seeking authorization to
                    vote for, his present instructions being to abstain. <persName
                        corresp="#p_TSIANGTF1">Tsiang</persName> is noncommittal but expects
                    instructions by noon Tuesday.</p>
                <p>Big Five meeting set for 4 p.m. Tuesday, March 31, with <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> meeting on Wednesday morning. Request instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
